# Core tiles

- [ ] `.direction` getter/setter
  - [ ] changes the layout and re-detect past DOM nodes.
- [ ] `.detect()`
  - [ ] Contributes a newly-added DOM tile, or detects moving X/Y and resizing.
  - [ ] Or contributes a newly-added DOM group, or detects label change.
- [ ] `.remove()`
  - [ ] Removes a tile (by its DOM node) or group after a transition. Returns a promise which fulfills after the transition is done. The end user has to manually remove the DOM node.

## Group label

- [ ] Editing

## Tile drag-n-drop

- [ ] Touch start
  - [ ] Trigger click
  - [ ] Trigger check
  - [ ] Trigger drag-n-drop (long-held)
- [ ] Mouse down
  - [ ] Trigger click
  - [ ] Trigger check
  - [ ] Trigger drag-n-drop (after short-delta)

More:

- [ ] While dragging a tile, enable overflow clipping at the groupTiles div.
  - [ ] When drag ends, still leave overflow clipping active for around 750 ms.
- [ ] When a group gets empty after drag end, remove it.

